<title>FRANCE: Accor extends Portuguese hotel venture.</title>
<headline>Accor extends Portuguese hotel venture.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>French hotels group Accor said on Monday that it was extending a cooperation agreement with Amorin of Portugal through the creation of a 50/50 joint venture.</p>
<p>The joint venture will speed up hotel development in Portugal by putting existing operations under the Mercure brand, expanding the Ibis chain, which now has 10 units, and the launch of the Formule 1 network, as well as the Coralia and Thalassa brands, Accor said in a statement.</p>
<p>It gave no financial details.</p>
